### ========================================================================
### AGENTS EXAMPLES - Wzorce agentow AI
### ========================================================================
###
### 1. PROMPT CHAINING - sekwencyjne przetwarzanie (analyze -> improve -> refactor)
### 2. ROUTING - klasyfikacja i kierowanie do specjalistycznych handlerow
### 3. PARALLELIZATION - rownolegle wykonywanie niezaleznych analiz
### 4. ORCHESTRATOR-WORKERS - dynamiczna dekompozycja i integracja zadan
### 5. EVALUATOR-OPTIMIZER - iteracyjna poprawa z petla zwrotna
###
### ========================================================================

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. PROMPT CHAINING - lancuch promptow dla Code Review
### Sekwencja: Analyze -> Improve -> Refactor
### Wyjscie kroku N staje sie wejsciem kroku N+1
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Chain: Prosty kod z bledami - metoda zwraca void ale ma return
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/chain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "public void foo() { int x = 1; return x; }"
}

### Chain: Kod z wieloma problemami - magic numbers, brak walidacji
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/chain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "public double calculate(int a, int b) { if(b == 0) return -999; return a * 3.14159 / b + 100; }"
}

### Chain: Kod z code smells - dluga metoda, brak obslugi bledow
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/chain
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "public void processUser(String name, String email, int age) { System.out.println(name); System.out.println(email); System.out.println(age); if(age > 18) { System.out.println(\"Adult\"); } else { System.out.println(\"Minor\"); } String upper = name.toUpperCase(); System.out.println(upper); }"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. ROUTING - klasyfikacja ticketow i kierowanie do specjalistow
### Kategorie: BILLING, TECHNICAL, SALES, GENERAL
### LLM klasyfikuje na podstawie kontekstu, nie prostych regul
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Route: BILLING - problem z platnością
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "I was charged twice for my subscription last month and I need a refund"
}

### Route: TECHNICAL - blad w aplikacji
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "I cannot login to my account. The page shows error 500 and then redirects to blank screen"
}

### Route: SALES - pytanie o cennik i funkcjonalnosci
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "What features are included in the Enterprise plan? Can you compare it with the Pro plan?"
}

### Route: GENERAL - ogolne pytanie / feedback
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/route
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "I love your product! Just wanted to share some ideas for new features you might consider"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. PARALLELIZATION - rownolegle analizy kodu
### 3 niezalezne analizy: Quality, Security, Performance
### Wyniki agregowane z ocena wazona (40% quality, 35% security, 25% performance)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Parallel: Kod z SQL injection - test bezpieczenstwa
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/parallel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceCode": "public List<User> findUsers(String name) { String sql = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = '\" + name + \"'\"; return jdbcTemplate.query(sql, userMapper); }",
  "language": "Java",
  "context": "Service wyszukujacy uzytkownikow po nazwie"
}

### Parallel: Kod z problemami wydajnosci - N+1 i brak cachowania
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/parallel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceCode": "public List<OrderDTO> getOrders() { List<Order> orders = orderRepository.findAll(); return orders.stream().map(o -> new OrderDTO(o.getId(), o.getCustomer().getName(), o.getItems().size())).toList(); }",
  "language": "Java",
  "context": "Endpoint zwracajacy liste zamowien z danymi klienta"
}

### Parallel: Czysty kod - baseline dla porownania
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/parallel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceCode": "public Optional<User> findById(Long id) { Objects.requireNonNull(id, \"User ID cannot be null\"); return userRepository.findById(id); }",
  "language": "Java",
  "context": "Prosta metoda wyszukiwania uzytkownika po ID"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. ORCHESTRATOR-WORKERS - dekompozycja projektu
### Orchestrator: analizuje request -> tworzy plan -> integruje wyniki
### Workers: wykonuja poszczegolne zadania (respektujac zaleznosci)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Orchestrate: Budowa REST API dla todo app
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/orchestrate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "Build a REST API for a todo application with CRUD operations. Include entity, repository, service and controller layers."
}

### Orchestrate: Implementacja systemu uwierzytelniania
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/orchestrate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "Implement a simple JWT authentication system with login endpoint, token generation and validation"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. EVALUATOR-OPTIMIZER - iteracyjna generacja kodu
### Petla: Generate -> Evaluate -> Improve (max 3 iteracje)
### Kryteria: Correctness(30%), Readability(20%), Efficiency(20%), Maintainability(20%), Security(10%)
### Akceptacja gdy score >= 0.8
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Optimize: Funkcja sprawdzajaca palindrom
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/optimize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "Write a Java function to check if a string is a palindrome. Handle edge cases like null, empty string, and ignore case/spaces."
}

### Optimize: Funkcja sortowania babelkowego z optymalizacja
POST http://localhost:8080/agents/optimize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userPromptText": "Write an optimized bubble sort implementation in Java that stops early if the array is already sorted"
}
